e:IspeChal - 4.jpg|Sefid Chah\nFile:Mon - An old stony village in Damavand volcano - panoramio.jpg|Old stony cave\nFile:\u067e\u0644 \u062c\u0645\u0639\u0647 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u0627\u0631 (\u062e\u0634\u062a \u067e\u0644) \u062c\u0648\u06cc\u0628\u0627\u0631.JPG|Jomeh Bazaar bridge\n</gallery>\n\n==Sister provinces==\n* {{flagicon|RUS}} [[Astrakhan Oblast|Astrakhan]]\n* {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Marche]]\n* {{flagicon|TAN}} [[Dar es Salaam]]\n* {{flagicon|Kyrgyzstan}} [[Issyk-Kul Region|Issyk-Kul]]\n* {{flagicon|Vietnam}} [[Mekong Delta]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Tapurian people]]  ''Mazandarani people''.\n* [[List of Mazanderanis]]\n* [[Maziar]]\n* {{C|Alborz (mountain range)|Alborz (''Elburz'') mountain range topics}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|26em}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{cite book|author= [[Vasily Bartold|W. Barthold]] |others=Translated by [[Svat Soucek]] |title=An Historical Geography of Iran|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Baz_AwAAQBAJ |publisher= Princeton University Press |isbn=978-1-4008-5322-9 |year=1984\n|chapter= Gilan and Mazandaran\n|pages= 230\u2013242\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|position=right}}\n* [http://www.ostan-mz.ir/ Official website]\n* [https://instagram.com/mazendron?igshid=12z0yhmjlzu5b]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20161011185336/http://www.mchto.ir/ Mazandaran Cultural Heritage Organization]\n* [http://mazandaran.irib.ir/ Official website of Mazandaran TV]\n* {{cite web |editor = [[Houchang E. Chehabi]] |work= Bibliographia Iranica |publisher= Iranian Studies Group at [[MIT]] |location=USA |title= Regional Studies: Mazandaran |url= http://web.mit.edu/isg/iranica.html }} (Bibliography)\n* [https://www.sabteahval.ir/mz/Default.aspx Registration Mazandaran]\n* A Mazandarani folk-song sung by [[Shusha Guppy]] in the 1970s: [http://www.iranian.com/ram/Shusha/15.ram ''Darling Dareyne'']\n\n{{Mazandaran Province}}\n{{Provinces of Iran}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mazandaran Province}}\n[[Category:Mazandaran Province| ]]\n[[Category:Provinces of Iran]]\n[[Category:Alborz (mountain range)]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the M\u0101zandar\u0101n Province of Iran|the Historic Tabarestan region|Tabaristan|region mentioned in Shahnameh|Mazandaran (Shahnameh)}}\n{{short description|Province of Iran}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = M\u0101zandar\u0101n Province\n| native_name                     = {{lang|fa|\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0645\u0627\u0632\u0646\u062f\u0631\u0627\u0646}}\n| native_name_lang                = fa<!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. \"fa\" for Persian -->\n| settlement_type                 = [[Provinces of Iran|Province]]\n| image_skyline                   = Selected Mazandaran.JPG\n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| image_map                       = Mazandaran.svg\n| image_map1                      = IranMazandaran-SVG.svg\n| map_caption                     = Counties of Mazandaran Province\n| map_caption1                    = Location of Mazandaran Province in Iran\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|36.5656|53.0588|region:IR_type:adm1st|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint                   = \n| coordinates_footnotes           = \n| subdivision_type                = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Iran}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Regions of Iran|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = Region 1<ref name=\"hamshahrionline.ir\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hamshahrionline.ir/details/263382/Iran/-provinces |title=\u0647\u0645\u0634\u0647\u0631\u06cc \u0622\u0646\u0644\u0627\u06cc\u0646-\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631 \u0628\u0647 \u06f5 \u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0647 \u062a\u0642\u0633\u06cc\u0645 \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |access-date=2014-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140623191332/http://www.hamshahrionline.ir/detai