ille and Memphis\n* [[Books Kinokuniya|Kinokuniya]]\n* Mardel Christian Stores\n* [[Powell's Books]], which includes the world's largest independent new and used bookstore\n* [[Schuler Books & Music]]\n* [[Tattered Cover]]\n\n===Defunct===\n<!-- DO NOT add names of bookstore chains to this list unless they already have Wikipedia articles, or could reasonably be expected to be the subject of an article or article section based on their notability NOW. For businesses not linked to their own articles, you MUST add at least one reference from a reliable source indicating their notability as a chain bookstore, or the business WILL be removed. This is not a directory of businesses! -->\n* Atlantic Books, discount chain on the [[East Coast]], defunct as of 2012<ref>{{cite web|last=Rosen |first=Judith |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/bookselling/article/49507-atlantic-books-to-close.html |title=Atlantic Books to Close |website=Publishersweekly.com |date=2011-11-14 |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref>\n* [[B. Dalton]]\n* Book World, Inc\n* [[Borders Group|Borders Books and Music]], also operated [[Brentano's]] \n* [[Coles (bookstore)|Coles...The Book People]]\n* [[Crown Books]]\n* [[Davis-Kidd Booksellers]]\n* [[Encore Books]]\n* [[Family Christian Stores]] - closed all locations in 2017\n* [[Hastings Entertainment]]\n* [[Kroch's and Brentano's]]\n* [[Media Play]]\n* Mr. Paperback, 10 stores in [[Maine]], defunct as of 2012<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://bangordailynews.com/2012/02/24/business/mr-paperback-stores-to-close-magazines-inc-to-be-sold-120-to-lose-jobs/ |title=Mr. Paperback stores to close, Magazines Inc. to be sold, 120 to lose jobs \u2014 Business \u2014 Bangor Daily News \u2014 BDN Maine |website=Bangordailynews.com |date=2012-02-24 |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref>\n* [[Oxford Bookstore]], offline chain of bookstores in the U.S.\n* [[Waldenbooks]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of independent bookstores]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\